title: Gov. Nixon appoints new Taney County Associate Circuit Judge

organizations.name: taney county associate circuit judge      r. tiffany yarnell

text:
R. Tiffany Yarnell , of Forsyth , as Associate Circuit Judge for Taney County. The appointment fills the vacancy created when the Honorable Tony Williams   for the 46 th Judicial Circuit. 
Yarnell has been the Chief Assistant   Taney County since January 2013 and has been an assistant prosecutor with the office since 2007. Prior to joining the Taney County Prosecuting Attorney’s Office, she was an assistant prosecutor with the Greene County Prosecuting Attorney’s Office. Her court room experience has included dozens of felony bench and jury trials, including first-degree murder trials. Yarnell obtained her   School of Law and her   Columbia College. 
“Tiffany Yarnell’s years of experience in the courtroom and her skills as a prosecutor will be a valuable asset in serving the people of Taney County from the bench,” Gov. Nixon said. “I am pleased to appoint her to serve as the newest Associate Circuit Judge in Taney County.” Related News
